Patch Set 1: Workflow-1

This gives me the following on the task:

 | message    | Copied 500 MiB

I dunno if it's legit to update that, but I don't really see it being
used anywhere else. This not only gives the operator some details that it's really running, but should be updating the updated_at on the task (too frequently, but this is good for testing).

So, if this seems reasonable, then we can use this to at least facilitate liveness checking of the task for lock-busting purposes. Perhaps we could even write a liveness check into the task_info structure so that we're not fooled by anything else updating the task itself.
